Avagelo GEOLDISIS, etc., v. John D. NAGLE, as Commissioner of Immigration for the Port of San Francisco. No. 6735. Circuit Court of Appeals, Ninth Circuit. May 19, 1932. Philip M. Zwerin, of San Francisco, Cal., for appellant. Geo. J. Hatfield, U. S. Atty., and Arthur Phelan, U. S. Immigration Service, both of San Francisco, Cal., for appellee.

Before WILBUR and SAWTELLE, Circuit Judges, and NETERER, District Judge.

PER CURIAM.

Upon motion of counsel for appellee, ordered appeal dismissed for failure to print record and file brief; mandate forthwith.
